**Pattern**: Tool-Using Agent
**Type**: Foundational + Integration
**Framework Support**: Google ADK (MCP Tools), CrewAI (Tools)

**Key Characteristics**:
- **System Integration**: Connects LLMs to real-world systems
- **Action Capability**: Executes operations beyond text generation
- **Tool Selection**: Intelligently chooses appropriate tools
- **Multi-System**: Orchestrates across multiple services

**Business Value**:
- **Automation**: Transforms insights into actions
- **Real-time Data**: Accesses live system information
- **Enterprise Integration**: Connects to existing infrastructure
- **Compliance**: Built-in audit trails and security

**Use Cases**:
- Supply chain optimization
- Financial reconciliation
- Inventory management
- CRM automation
- ERP orchestration
- API coordination

**Real Example**:
ManufactureCo deployed tool-using agents for supply chain optimization, achieving 43% reduction in stockouts, 21% decrease in inventory costs, and $2.3M annual savings.

**When to Use**:
- Multi-system orchestration needed
- Real-time data access required
- Actions must be executed
- Enterprise system integration
- Compliance and audit trails important

**MCP Protocol Benefits**:
- **Standardized**: Consistent tool interface
- **Secure**: Built-in authentication and authorization
- **Auditable**: Complete action logs
- **Scalable**: Easy to add new tools
